      "role": "user",
      "content": "i mean i get that text a is more formal, but isn't \"intelligence\" more about the actual logic and the quality of the ideas being presented rather than just the words used? if a scholar was writing in a dialect like the one in text b, would they actually be seen as less intelligent by their peers, or is that just a social prejudice? i'm trying to figure out if the \"competence\" you're talking about is actually tied to the person's intellect or just their ability to mimic a specific way of speaking.",
